// Hello World (helloworld) - simplest benchmark
// ===================================================================

42 = 42


// ===================================================================
// BLOCKED BENCHMARKS - require compiler bug fixes
// ===================================================================
//
// nsieve, spectral_norm, matmul are blocked by a tail call optimization bug:
//
// Bug: Lists built by TAIL-RECURSIVE functions get corrupted when modified.
// Non-tail-recursive list building works correctly.
//
// Corrupts: def repeat(v, n, acc) = repeat(v, n-1, [v, ...acc])  // tail-recursive
// Works:    def repeat(v, n) = [v, ...repeat(v, n-1)]            // non-tail-recursive
//
// List.repeat and List.setAt both use tail recursion, triggering corruption.
// The tail call optimization appears to incorrectly reuse memory for cons cells.
